<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[tepples]]></name></author>
<updated>2016-11-06T13:44:19+00:00</updated>
<published>2016-11-06T13:44:19+00:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=15073&amp;p=182425#p182425</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=15073&amp;p=182425#p182425"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: What is wrong with the NES Classic Edition noise emulati]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=15073&amp;p=182425#p182425"><![CDATA[
Then the bootloader itself would disqualify the &quot;suitable mechanism&quot;. Shipping on actual mask ROM is OK because the user cannot physically install updates, but if the user can overwrite sectors, the user can install modified library files. It's explicit in LGPLv3 with its &quot;Installation Information&quot; clause, but present implicitly in LGPLv2.<br /><br />This is as much flash as the Wii has.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun Nov 06, 2016 1:44 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
