<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=15073&amp;p=182424#p182424</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=15073&amp;p=182424#p182424"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: What is wrong with the NES Classic Edition noise emulati]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=15073&amp;p=182424#p182424"><![CDATA[
Key words &quot;if the user installs one&quot;. If the chip is read-only, or signed and checked by a bootloader, they cannot install one.<br /><br />This is the Tivoization that is prevented by both GPLv3 and LGPLv3. The program would operate correctly if there wasn't this external mechanism blocking the user from installing a new library <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7237">calima</a> — Sun Nov 06, 2016 1:10 pm</p><hr />
